steps.text:
Use logical-line cursor commands in `keybindings.json`:

```json
{
  "key": "ctrl+alt+down",
  "command": "editor.action.insertCursorBelow",
  "args": { "logicalLine": true }
},
{
  "key": "ctrl+alt+up",
  "command": "editor.action.insertCursorAbove",
  "args": { "logicalLine": true }
}
```

This skips word-wrapped display segments and adds cursors on actual document lines—the behavior shown in the second GIF. It’s already supported by the editor’s multicursor actions, so no source change was needed.
